var messages=[["You find nothing. You decide to keep looking."],["You stumble upon a locked door. You do not hold the key."],["You have a funny feeling like you're being followed."],["Your curiosity is peaked. You refresh the page."],["You turn around to look behind you and find yet more nothing."],["You care enough to open this website."],["You discover that you may be lost."],["You are greeted by nothing at all."],["The pit beckons, yet it is empty."],["Is the glass half full? No, it is completely empty."],["'easter egg'"],["sudo rm -rf --no-preserve-root /"],["グーグル翻訳"],["Gonna start practicing bhop_badges so i get that sub 18."],["Has Anyone Really Been Far Even as Decided to Use Even Go Want to do Look More Like?"],["I wrote this at 2:37 in the morning."],["https://smol.fi"],["Please don't wget me."],["You find a refridgerator. It contains a single bottle of nothing."],["December 13th, 1989."],["If there were a place lower than here, it would surely be hell."],["It's fine even if you're useless right now. As long as you keep looking towards the future, I'm sure a day will come when you'll find your worth."],["I wonder why it is, that people fall in love with others? I think that to seek out love even when you already have a nice family is being greedy. No matter how much you like another person, you can never be with that person forever... But I dislike that. I don't care if I have to throw away everything else. I just want you to look at me."],["True happiness only lasts for a brief time, so you better enjoy it while you can, right?"],["What do you think are the most important things in life? Money, dreams, sympathy towards others... Yes, they're all important things as well... But the most important thing is responsibility for your own actions."],["There're a lot of people who want to be in despair just so they can pity themselves."],["Freedom without any purpose feels a whole lot like boredom."],["Isn't it better to regret things you've done, than regret things you've never even tried?"],["The world is drowning in weirdness and lies......and here we are, so used to it that we're actually bored!"],["When you're sincere about doing something, you're stalked by the fear that there's no turning back."],["...back then the sky seemed so vast. And now the sky above me... is low, and narrow, and heavy."],["I always thought I wasn't afraid to die. No... No one is afraid of death itself. Your pain and suffering is over in an instant. What really makes me suffer... Is seeing you crying over me."],["We were like visitors to some strange planet."],["If only the last dozen years were just a dream my younger self was having, how wonderful that would be."],["Who cares what we dream about? Just getting through each day is hard enough."],["The love song I wrote that day... I got embarrassed and never sang it for her. Oh yeah... I'll sing it to her when I go home. I'll go home. I'll hurry home."],["What if everything in the world were a misunderstanding, what if laughter were really tears?"],["At that moment, beauty itself struck me as a kind of painful melancholy."],["I was drawn to all the wrong things: I liked to drink, I was lazy, I didn't have a god, politics, ideas, ideals. I was settled into nothingness; a kind of non-being, and I accepted it. I didn't make for an interesting person. I didn't want to be interesting, it was too hard. What I really wanted was only a soft, hazy space to live in, and to be left alone. On the other hand, when I got drunk I screamed, went crazy, got all out of hand. One kind of behavior didn't fit the other. I didn't care."],["A man who drinks too much on occasion is still the same man as he was sober. An alcoholic, a real alcoholic, is not the same man at all. You can't predict anything about him for sure except that he will be someone you never met before."],["I'm gonna get drunk and make websites."],["A drinking man's someone who wants to forget he isn't still young and believing."],["Most experts point out, strong motivations for avoiding drugs; but there are also strong motivations for taking them. People who claim not to understand why anyone would get addicted to drugs are usually people who haven't tried them or who are genetically fairly invulnerable to them."],["I never told you this, but I love you. Really."],["I didn't want to wake up. I was having a much better time asleep. And that's really sad. It was almost like a reverse nightmare, like when you wake up from a nightmare you're so relieved. I woke up into a nightmare."],["But in the end one needs more courage to live than to kill himself."],["“Did you really want to die?” “No one commits suicide because they want to die.”"],["Sometimes even to live is an act of courage."],["and he suddenly knew that if she killed herself, he would die. Maybe not immediately, maybe not with the same blinding rush of pain, but it would happen. You couldn't live for very long without a heart."],["The thought of suicide is a great consolation: by means of it one gets through many a dark night."],["There comes a time when you look into the mirror and you realize that what you see is all that you will ever be. And then you accept it. Or you kill yourself. Or you stop looking in mirrors."],["I went to the worst of bars hoping to get killed but all I could do was to get drunk again."],["Killing oneself is, anyway, a misnomer. We don't kill ourselves. We are simply defeated by the long, hard struggle to stay alive. When somebody dies after a long illness, people are apt to say, with a note of approval, “He fought so hard.” And they are inclined to think, about a suicide, that no fight was involved, that somebody simply gave up. This is quite wrong."],["I envy people that know love. That have someone who takes them as they are."],["More than the sound of my own beating heart, I miss the sound of a ticking clock. Time passes. It must pass..."],["Among my stillness was a pounding heart."],["I'm afraid my voice is going to break. I am afraid she is going to hear how much this hurts."],["I feel the monster of grief again, writhing in the empty space where my heart and stomach used to be. I gasp, pressing both palms to my chest. Now the monstrous thing has its claws around my throat, squeezing my airway. I twist and put my head between my knees, breathing until the strangled feeling leaves me."],["You know what truly aches? Having so much inside you and not having the slightest clue of how to pour it out."],["I'd broken myself apart. And I didn't think even eternity would be long enough to fix me."],["If we had happy endings, we’d all be under gravestones now."],["I'll use the blood from my spilling heart to write the words that were never able to slip out of my mouth, so you can see how much you've broken me into a perpetual state of melancholy."],["I used to feel like i was on the top of the world. Then one day, i noticed that it felt like i was no longer on the top of the world. I was just floating around inside of it. And then eventually, it felt like the world was on top of me."],["May you see with eyes of light in everdark, may your mind walk free and unfettered amongst all, touching wisely and well, may you go in peace. But wait for me, beloved."],["I'm so good at beginnings, but in the end I always seem to destroy everything, including myself."],["The thing about a spiral is, if you follow it inward, it never actually ends. It just keeps tightening, infinitely."],["Out of suffering have emerged the strongest souls; the most massive characters are seared with scars."],["Should you shield the canyons from the windstorms you would never see the true beauty of their carvings."],["At some point we all look up and realize we are lost in a maze."],["Everything you can imagine is real."],["I'm killing time while I wait for life to shower me with meaning and happiness."],["If people sat outside and looked at the stars each night, I'll bet they'd live a lot differently."],["I find my life is a lot easier the lower I keep my expectations."],["I think we dream so we don't have to be apart so long. If we're in each other's dreams, we can play together all night."],["That's one of the remarkable things about life. It's never so bad that it can't get worse."],["I don’t know what’s worse: to not know what you are and be happy, or to become what you’ve always wanted to be, and feel alone."],["Every form of addiction is bad, no matter whether the narcotic be alcohol, morphine or idealism."],["It was a bright cold day in April, and the clocks were striking thirteen."],["Your worst enemy, he reflected, was your nervous system. At any moment the tension inside you was liable to translate itself into some visible symptom."],["When it is dark enough, you can see the stars."],["I knew nothing but shadows and I thought them to be real."],["Turn on the dark, I'm afraid of the light."],["The world is quiet here."],["I was quiet, but I was not blind."],["Sometimes you need to sit lonely on the floor in a quiet room in order to hear your own voice and not let it drown in the noise of others."],["I like it where it gets dark at night, and if you want noise, you have to make it yourself."],["Solitude is a catalyst for innovation."],["The world is too quiet without you nearby."],["It's always worse than it seems."],["There is no greater sorrow than to recall in misery the time when we were happy."],["Deep inside, where nothing is fine, I've lost my mind."],["It's a lot like drowning, except I can see people breathing around me."],["From the moment we are born, we begin to die."],["Clicking my lighter, I grant myself death and the will to live."],["and there you have it, another body on the floor surrounded by things that don't mean much to anyone except to the one who can't take any of them along."],["After all, suicide is contagious."],["Whether the people are happy or not in their lives, they have learned to keep steadily moving, moving all the time."],["Please, please."],["Hasn't it been a long time since you had a flying dream?"],["In town, there's a tiny beach that's never busy, not even in the summer. I used to like walking there, looking for stuff. Like old fireworks. Or kelp. A hat knocked off someone's head by the wind. You basically never find what you were expecting to. And maybe you weren't expecting to find anything right from the start."],["There's a lot of beauty to be found in sadness and melancholia. One of the things that you find time and time again - not just with music, but with literature - is that things that appear to be quite depressing on the surface can ironically be very uplifting and touching to other people. When you hear something that really reminds you that you're not alone in feeling sad, depressed, melancholic, angry - I think that can actually be a very cathartic experience."],["Solitude is the house of peace."],["The night is the hardest time to be alive and 4am knows all my secrets."],["Melancholy were the sounds on a winter's night."],["People who go to bed early always complain that the night is too short, but for those who stay up all night, it can feel as long as a lifetime."],["I had a dream about you last night. I was alone on a dark night and you came to me as a firefly. I knew it was you because you were the brightest."],["Solitude is fine but you need someone to tell that solitude is fine."],["If you're lonely when you're alone, you're in bad company."],["I hope you never have to think about anything as much as I think about you."],["Each day without solitude weakened me. I took no pride in my solitude; but I was dependent on it. The darkness of the room was like sunlight to me."],["If a man cannot understand the beauty of life, it is probably because life never understood the beauty in him."],["Loneliness is the poverty of self; solitude is richness of self."],["Solitude has soft, silky hands, but with strong fingers it grasps the heart and makes it ache with sorrow."],["Find meaning. Distinguish melancholy from sadness."],["Find what you love and let it kill you."],["Stop smoking, we love you."],["I just wanted you to know... That I tried."],["Life sucks, you know? And yet, I still want to live."],["It seems like everyone is moving forward. I guess I should get moving too."],["I'm troubled, you know."],["What a wonderful world!"],["I'm scared... I'll wake up from my dream if I fall asleep."],["But no matter how hard he cried, he was still all alone on this earth."],["Everybody dies, death is unbiased. But still, we all keep building things up, only for them to fall down again. Whatever for?"],["It's a life of boring happiness."],["We've got no light of hope in our future. Nothing is going to happen."],["He says the butterflies have come to snatch us away. They're going to take us off to eternity, he says."],["Where am I to go from here?"],["There's a loneliness that's part of living as a human being, that you can never get rid of."],["...when this song ends, I'll go back to my usual life. ...Ah, the song is ending..."],["Could you go home without me? I'd like to stay here for a bit."],["We did not hold hands like we did yesterday anymore."],['There is no more of the usual "see you tomorrow". That is just how it is. You have no more need to come to this place anymore. And neither do I.'],["I have always thought you are so beautiful."],["I've been riding on here for a few years already, haven't I?"],["Good night."],["Thank you for all your hard work."],["No matter how hard you try to forget it or hide it, it's always there, deep inside."],["Before long, the bus stopped at a familiar bus stop. Without a sound, the doors opened, and several passengers boarded, as though being swallowed."],["No matter how light your make-up may be, once it melts you will look ugly. So, no matter how hurt you feel, you cannot cry."],["Lately, the memories from now and before are getting blurry, like a fog moving in."],["I think my place is out there somewhere, but I can't remember clearly. When did I start riding this bus?"],["There's no point. There's just no point to any of it."],["Does that hurt? Of course it hurts. But there are people who suffer more in this world."],["I'm sorry. Please don't look like that. You were always prettiest when you smiled."],["It's a distant world. The me of before never imagined the me of today either. That was already years ago. If I think about it, it was a difficult time. There are still scars left on my body from that time. I forget about them everyday, though."],["It's tough for anyone to live their life. I know that. But as I am now, I feel powereless."],["Everything seemed to exist in a miraculous balance."],["As usual, the train this morning is jam-packed with expressionless people going wherever it is they go. Will I be one of those people someday?"],["Wait, I'm not dreaming anymore, right? Right..."],["These last few days, I've had this strange sense of relief."],["It's so peaceful up here."],["I am just fine again today."],["You remind me of a poem I can't remember, and a song that my never have existed, and a place I'm not sure I've ever been to."]];function displayMessage(){document.getElementById("message").innerHTML=messages[Math.random()*messages.length|0]}window.onload=displayMessage();